commit.message:
Workaround for Qt bug in a context menu invoked by Menu key (#960)

`QContextMenuEvent` reports the cursor position incorrectly when a context menu is invoked by Menu key in detailed list mode, i.e., in `QTreeView`. Since the bug has nasty effects for us, a small workaround is included.

Closes https://github.com/lxqt/pcmanfm-qt/issues/1882

commit.message:
Started Qt6 port (#778)

* Started Qt6 port

* Focus the text entry of new-file dialog

Qt did it before Qt 6.6.1. Now it needs to be done explicitly.

* Also focus the text entry of overwrite dialog explicitly

Qt did it before Qt 6.6.1. Now it needs to be done explicitly.

I think this is a regression in Qt 6.6.1: the first focusable widget should be focused automatically, as it was always so. But the workaround is a harmless short line; hence adding it.

* Removed `qAsConst`

And bumped minimum required version of Qt to 6.6.0

* Silence new warnings of GLib ≥ 2.76

Apparently, GLib has become more strict; hence the warnings.

commit.message:
Get terminals list also from data directories (#924)

The files `terminals.list` inside data directories take priority over the one provided by `libfm-qt` if existing. How data directories are handled is left to Glib.

In this way, the user can create `~/.local/share/libfm-qt/terminals.list` and see the result in PCManFM-Qt on the fly. (Later, PCManFM-Qt might be patched to create or append to that file.)

Closes https://github.com/lxqt/libfm-qt/issues/922

commit.message:
Fixed a crash on deleting pathbar (#920)

The crash would happen if a pathbar was deleted while its path-edit had focus (e.g., by pressing F6 inside path-edit in pcmanfm-qt). The reason is explained in the code comment.

Fixes https://github.com/lxqt/libfm-qt/issues/919
